{
  "texts": [
    "The electronic occupation of a spin-up electron is given by:|n ↑ (t)⟩ = b 2 (t)e -iω0t |2, 0⟩+ ∞ -∞dω q b 1,q (t)e -iωqt |1, ω q ⟩.",
    "(B3) Here, the ket |2, 0⟩ denotes the state of the conduction electron with kinetic energy ε 2 = -2t 0 cos(π/2) = 0 and no magnons in the localized spin chain, while |1, ω q ⟩ represents the state of the conduction electron with kinetic energy ε 1 = -2t 0 cos(π/2-∆k) ≈ -J/2 (two-fold degenerate) and a magnons contained in the spin chain, with with energy ω q /2.",
    "Here, b 2 (t) and b 1q (t) represent the probability amplitudes for the kets |2, 0⟩ and |1, ω q ⟩, respectively, and ω 0 is the energy transferred to the bath.",
    "Due to the initial condition, the system is prepared completely in the excited state |2, 0⟩ at t = 0, implying that: b 2 (t = 0) = 1, b 1q (t = 0) = 0.",
    "(B4)To characterize the interaction between the TLS and the bosonic bath, we need to solve a set of coupled differential equations given by:ḃ2 = -i γ π ∞ -∞dω q f (ω q)e -i(ωq-ω0)t b 1q, (B5a) ḃ1q = -i γ π f (ω q)e -i(ωq-ω0)t b 2, (B5b)where the parameter 2γ characterizes the decay rate of the excited state in the Markovian limit."
  ]
}